  What is WebSocket?

A WebSocket is a communication protocol that provides:

👉 Full-duplex communication (both client & server can send data anytime)
👉 Over a single persistent connection

Client sends HTTP request
Server upgrades it to WebSocket
Connection stays open
Both can send messages anytime

example:WhatsApp chat 💬
Online gaming 🎮
Live stock market 📈
Notifications 🔔
